reviews.review_text: Bertha The Oade sources are the best.  If you think they sound flat like the reviewer of the other aud recording, just adjust your equalizer a bit.  The Oade recordings offer much fuller sound and really give you the sense of being there.

Baby Blue Cut? I have the FOB source and the Oade Source for this show and on each recording the Baby Blue is cut in about the same place. Particularly sad because this is quite a nice version. What's the deal did everyones cassette run out of tape at this point?

Otherwise great show overall ( a few lows ) and above average AUD's of this performance. worth the download. 1st set is the highlight.

their not the best that they do,their the only ones that do what they do! a couple of years back i would listen to this show on a terrible quality tape, but i loved it. its great to hear this in better sound. there are great highlights, like the stranger, eyes and the energy is worth the listen

Ehhh Sound quality isn't bad but the boys were not up to par this show. Did anyone notice Jerry trying to to go into Lazy Lightning about 10 times? It seemed like the rest of the band (mainly Bobby) were basically ignoring him or spacing out. 

I give a 3 though for sound quality and set list.
